verbose_text: One possible explanation of the selective transfer of IgG across the placental barrier for our findings may be that FCGRT of the syncytiotrophoblast transports both ligands but FCGR2B2 of the placental endothelium allows only IgG to pass.
evidence: FCGRT of the syncytiotrophoblast transports both ligands but FCGR2B2 of the placental endothelium allows only IgG
